Information Vech Check is an app that is used to carry out safety inspection on a heavy goods vehicle or trailer. This helps to stay compliant with requirements of the VOSA or DVA as all defects that occur are noted and future defects can be prevented. Checkbox- Check the corresponding checkbox if the feature has no defect present. Leave blank if N/A (not applicable) to that vehicle or trailer Spanner button- Opens up information box for providing details on the corresponding defect. Each defect must be described and ranked according to its severity. A minor defect is one that A major defect is one that A critical defect is one that Key Finished Security of body, containers and crane support legs
